            . I have one partner. Collins gave an alarm, and I missed a sieve of apples; I saw the prisoner sitting on the sieve under the Piazzas - I called to him; he said he had left another man to pay for them - I was about to give charge of him, when a man stepped up and said, "Here is half-a-crown in part payment;" they had not been off the porter's head two minutes - they were not unpacked, nor fit for sale.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. I had dealt with Mr. Essex, Mr. Smith's partner, for them.</p>
